                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d888">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense(M)Turkey/947: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-03-18T13:00:00+02:00"
                            >March 18, 1944—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 1:19 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>484. See my 319, February 23. The Secretary General of Foreign Office informed me
                    last night that in response to the assurances given me by him that the movement
                    of chrome for British account would be materially increased, approximately 4,000
                    metric tons of 45 to 50 percent chrome ore had arrived Iskenderun during the
                    last few days and that the movement would continue.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
